// src/core/content-version.ts
// Single source of truth for the two manually-bumped cache-busting versions.
// Bump a constant when you make a change you want reflected in-game without the
// player having to clear storage or hit "New World".

/**
 * Bump when building/asset GENERATION changes (geometry, metric scale, blueprint
 * output). A baked sprite whose `recipeVersion` differs from this is treated as
 * STALE and skipped, so the live parametric generator renders instead.
 * Regenerate the base library at the new version to let baked art win again.
 * History: 'v2' retired the 'v1' baked art left metrically wrong by the
 * metric-scale standardization; 'v3' was the chroma-key sprite pipeline
 * (magenta-background img2img + keyed alpha); 'v4' changes the CACHED FORMAT —
 * the stored blob is now the processed sprite (keyed + registered to the
 * geometry mask + quantized, at final resolution) rather than the raw LLM PNG,
 * with validation gating what gets persisted at all; 'v5' is the adaptive
 * pipeline — negotiation-band registration, detail-inviting prompts, relaxed
 * IoU gate, and the rebuilt castle_keep + window features on tall presets;
 * 'v6' is the medieval detail pass — material-driven eaves/verges, half-hip
 * (gablet) roofs, dormers, ridge louvres, slimmer multi-chimneys, per-type
 * window programmes, rectangular plans (see
 * docs/reference/medieval-building-reference.md); 'v7' deepens the eaves —
 * material overhangs grown to real medieval depths (thatch 60 cm … slate
 * 20 cm) with sprocketed-eave drop capping so door heads stay clear;
 * 'v8' is the roof-slab remodel — roofs are individual sloped boards with real
 * thickness (projecting eaves AND verges read as boards, not a solid wedge) plus
 * recessed gable-end tympana, and masonry/metal ridge stacks are offset BESIDE
 * the ridge beam (timber smoke-louvres still straddle it) so chimneys no longer
 * pierce the structural ridge;
 * 'v9' — connectome Slice 1: a building's smoke vent is now DERIVED from its hearth
 * (early-medieval commoner dwellings — cottage/longhouse/yurt — get a period-correct
 * ridge louver, NOT a chimney; vents stripped from their presets and re-derived), so
 * cottage/longhouse/yurt geometry shifts;
 * 'v10' — generative openings: doors + windows are now DERIVED from the room graph
 * (exterior portals ⇒ doors, needs-light zones ⇒ windows, distributed by wall length +
 * era glazing) for presets tagged 'gen-openings' (cottage/shrine/guard_post/watermill/
 * temple_small migrated to fact-seeds), so their fenestration shifts.
 * 'v11' — procedural weathering: building/prop albedo is aged in `composeStructure`
 * (dirt pooling low, grime in AO crevices, vertical rain-streaks, rust blooming on
 * metal) via `src/assetgen/render/weathering.ts`; pure flora/rock left pristine.
 * 'v12' — lit windows: window panes are a new 'glass' material (dark cool albedo by
 * day) carrying a warm emissive, so the renderer glows them at night (emissive ×
 * nightFactor). Shifts the grey/material/emissive of any preset with windows.
 * 'v13' — real flora generators: trees/shrubs now grow recursive proctree branch
 * skeletons (broadleaf/weeping) or space-colonization crowns (conifer cones) keyed
 * on a per-species crownShape, replacing the six L-system recipes that collapsed all
 * species to ~3 silhouettes. Shifts the geometry of every `branch_plant` (plant) sprite.
 * 'v14' — layered-connectome Layer 1 (STRUCTURE): a building's frameType is now selected
 * from its wall material + era/region and GATES its form — a solid/cruck/stave wall can no
 * longer jetty (only a box-frame does), and storeys are capped to what the frame bears. So
 * any building whose authored massing exceeded its frame shifts (e.g. the stone manor's
 * cross-wing loses its timber-frame jetty). See the layered-connectome-expression spec.
 * 'v15' — layered-connectome Layer 2a (FORM): a `gen-form` body's vertical massing
 * (plan/levels/jetty/storeyM) is now DERIVED from the program + structure rather than
 * hand-listed — a box-frame dwelling stacks a jettied upper storey, a cruck one stays a
 * single low range. Migrated the dwelling family (cottage/tavern/townhouse); the cottage's
 * derived form matches its authored one, the box-frame inns/townhouses take the frame's
 * full jetty. Footprint held (placement unchanged). Shifts the box-frame dwellings' geometry.
 * 'v16' — layered-connectome Layer 3a (FABRIC): STRUCTURE now gates fabric. (1) The frame's
 * fenestration policy drives derived openings — a mass wall takes few, widely-spaced lights,
 * a box frame's panels glaze generously — so any `gen-openings` body's window count/spacing
 * shifts to the frame's rhythm (the cruck cottage loses a window; mass-wall buildings grow
 * austere). (2) A masonry wall-chimney requires a flue-capable frame: a cruck/stave build
 * can never grow a stone stack and keeps its ridge smokehole however late/rich. Footprint
 * held (placement unchanged). See the layered-connectome-expression spec.
 * 'v17' — layered-connectome Layer 2b (FORM footprint variety): a `gen-form` body's plan
 * LENGTH is now sized to a bay count picked from the program's `sizeBays` range by the
 * per-instance seed (a cottage is 1–2 bays, a tavern 2–3), CLAMPED to the authored footprint
 * so the lot — and placement — is unchanged. Two cottages on a street now read as a short
 * single-bay cot and a longer two-bay one rather than clones. The name-derived default
 * cottage resolves to a shorter single-bay body, so its geometry shifts (see
 * assetgen-golden). Pairs with the placer threading a per-instance seed (a WORLD bump, since
 * the generative catalogue→geometry bridge grows the FOOTPRINT itself per instance).
 * 'v18' — layered-connectome Layer 3b (bay-aware openings): a `gen-openings` body's WINDOWS now
 * snap to the structural bay CENTRES — the frame's `bayModule` (metres/bay) divides the wall run
 * into panels and a window lights one panel each (skipping the door's bay), instead of the old
 * fixed fractional slots. So fenestration sits where a real timber-frame/masonry wall carries it
 * (panels between posts/piers). Window COUNT is unchanged (still structure-gated by spacing/
 * maxPerFace) — only positions move, so footprint/placement hold. Shifts the pane positions of
 * any structure-annotated `gen-openings` body. See the layered-connectome-expression spec.
 * 'v19' — layered-connectome Layer 3b (undercroft/cellar): a buildingType that declares
 * `undercroft` (the burgage townhouse), built on a masonry-capable frame (mass-wall/box-frame)
 * and stacking ≥2 storeys, now renders its GROUND storey as a STONE base course carrying the
 * (timber) upper — `buildingFacets` splits the wall solid at the base-course height with a
 * Manifold boolean (stone band + wall-material upper). Only undercroft bodies change; every
 * other building's wall is byte-identical (the single-material path is the original code).
 * See the layered-connectome-expression spec.
 * 'v20' — E3 shrine-procession slice 1 (retire temple_small): the hand-tuned `temple_small`
 * preset is gone — a temple now EXPRESSES from its church-axial programme through the fold
 * (generative bridge → FORM → FABRIC), so its geometry is derived not pinned. The generative
 * bridge gains a SACRED-AXIAL footprint rule (a temple/shrine cella is DEEPER than wide, the
 * nave fronting the door with a pediment; an axial barn stays wide). Temples now vary their
 * footprint per instance. See the shrine-procession spec.
 * 'v21' — E3 axis-mundi spire: a WORSHIP building (temple/church/shrine — not a barn, told
 * apart by its single entrance vs the barn's opposed cart doors) now crowns its ridge with a
 * stone STEEPLE — a new `spire` ridge-feature kind (a slender shaft + a pointed conical cap),
 * derived in connectomeToBlueprint. Shifts the geometry of every worship building; dwellings/
 * barns are unchanged. See the shrine-procession spec.
 * 'v22' — E3 threshold stoup (Law 1): a new `stoup` prop (a stone pedestal + bored basin,
 * composed from raw prims — no new part renderer) — the holy-water cleansing basin co-placed
 * at a sacred precinct's border. Additive (a new prop recipe; existing baked art unaffected).
 */
export const ART_RECIPE_VERSION = 'v32';  // STAIR GEOMETRY UPGRADE: outdoor stairs stop reading as a plain box-ramp. The `stair_flight` blueprint part (`blueprint/parts/stair.ts`, presets stair_scramble/wood/stone/grand) and the mural wall stair (`assetgen/geometry/stair-spec.ts`) both gain: a proud NOSING lip per tread (top beads the band, overhang shades the riser via AO → step rhythm reads at native zoom), coursed SIDE CHEEKS (stringers massing the flight; a railed masonry side raises into a raking parapet, a timber side keeps a low stringer under balusters), and FOOT/HEAD blocks seating the flight into the ground. Steps + cheeks now carry masonry `work` coursing (dressed→ashlar, rough scramble→random_rubble; timber→plank/plank_v) so the analytic surface engine + banded lighting shade real per-stone variation instead of a flat grey face — no lighting painted into the albedo. The mural stair also DROPS its half-height burying stringer ramp (it hid the lower steps) so every tread is exposed. Compose OUTPUT changes for any stair (road stair props + defensive-ring mural stairs) ⇒ version bump; the golden fixtures (cottage, stone box) carry no stair so their G-buffer hashes hold. (v31 — HOLLOW CHIMNEY FLUE + CROWN LIP: masonry chimney stacks (vent kind `chimney`, both ridge + wall placement) now read as OPEN flues instead of capped pillars — a crown lip (`1.2·cw` square, 0.08 tall, same material) caps the stack and a flue recess (`0.52·cw` square, 0.15/~0.3 m deep) is subtracted from the top so the G-buffer shows a dark recessed mouth (which img2img then paints as an open flue). The stack body drops a crown-lip short of topZ so the crown sits WITHIN the existing protrusion — the vent anchor/topZ and CHIMNEY_PROTRUDE are unchanged (smoke emitter + mount-anchor mirror don't drift). Pipe/smokehole/spire vents keep their capped tops. Compose OUTPUT changes for any building with a chimney (tavern, smithy, bakehouse, cottage…) ⇒ version bump; the golden stone-box fixture (no vent) holds, the cottage moves (it carries a chimney). ALSO IN v31 — PAINT-PIPELINE SWAP: the img2img paint model is now qwen-image-edit-2511 on Replicate (`src/llm/building-image.ts` BUILDING_IMAGE_MODEL; structure-adherence pilot IoU 0.974–0.994 vs FLUX.2 Klein's 0.80), the silhouette-IoU quality gate tightens 0.7→0.9 to match (qwen preserves the input silhouette, so 0.9 rejects real drift instead of welcoming it), and the final quantize pass is the perceptual Oklab k-means + Bayer4 ordered dither (`quantizePaletteOklab`) instead of raw-sRGB bucketing. Cache keys embed the model id + this version, so every sprite reseeds at the new recipe. (v30 — STONE-LOWER-HALF WATERMILL + SUBMERGED WHEEL: a wet mill is built STONE up to the wheel storey (the load-bearing, splash-battered lower half) with a timber loft over it — so the `watermill` preset is now a 2-storey body carrying a FULL-STOREY (1.35-tile) stone `baseCourse` (stone ground floor / undercroft, tar-timber loft) instead of a single timber storey, and its waterwheel gains a `submerge` param (`structural.ts` waterwheel: `cz = radius − submerge`, default 0.1, preset 0.38) so the wheel's lower arc DIPS below the ground/waterline into the millrace instead of resting on it. Compose OUTPUT changes for the watermill only; the golden fixtures (cottage, stone box) hold. (v29 — WATERMILL WATERWHEEL + SACRED-SPIRE PROPORTIONING: the watermill gains its defining silhouette — a big vertical WATERWHEEL (new `waterwheel` composite prim/`solidWaterwheel`: twin annulus rims + radial spokes + hub + axle + circumferential paddle boards, one unioned timber solid; new `waterwheelPartType` mounts it OUTSIDE a chosen wall face, dipping to ~ground/water). The sacred spire is now SIZED to the building it crowns instead of a fixed `width:1.5`: a long nave carries a grounded broach WEST TOWER, but a short cell (a 2×2 wayside shrine) gets a slender ridge FLÈCHE — no fat tower swallowing the footprint (`solids.ts` spire vent). Buttresses are gated to a real masonry SPAN (footprint ≥4 tiles) so a tiny shrine no longer wears chunky corner piers (`body.ts`). Compose OUTPUT changes for the watermill (new wheel) + any small worship building with a spire/buttresses (shrine, church-axial cells) ⇒ version bump; the golden fixtures (cottage, stone box) hold. (v28 — PARISH-CHURCH SPIRE = PYRAMID (broach), not a cone: a new `pyramid` prim (`solids.ts` `solidPyramid` — a true 4-sided taper over an axis-aligned footprint) replaces the round cone cap on SQUARE towers + the sacred spire vent, so the four wall corners no longer poke up as a "bucket collar" around an inscribed cone. The `parish-church` preset drops its hand-placed offset `tower` PART (which pierced the nave roof, leaving a notch) — its west tower is now fully GENERATIVE: the church-axial connectome crowns the FULL-footprint nave's entrance gable with a centred square west tower + pyramid broach spire. Buttresses widened + heightened (chunky stone piers, not a thin picket-fence). Compose OUTPUT changes for any worship building with a spire vent (shrine, church-axial catalogue buildings) even where the SPEC is unchanged (cone→pyramid cap) ⇒ version bump required; the golden fixtures (plaster cottage, stone box — no spire/tower/buttress) hold. (v27 — TAVERN FRAME REWORK: exposed timber HALF-TIMBERING is now systemic — any `frame:true` rect body (`blueprint/parts/frame.ts`) renders its structural posts/rails/studs as raised dark-oak trim over plaster infill, and the frame READS its openings: rails break around every door/window, studs jamb the opening edges, and a door gets its head beam (no member runs blindly across a hole). Studding densified (ceil bays, 1.4-tile panels) so windowless back faces read as framed as the fenestrated fronts. Plus a stone PLINTH base course + shallower roof pitch on the tavern, and a trim retune (window sills + door knob project half as far). Only the tavern opts in; its composed sprite changes, and the golden cottage moves again from the trim retune. // WINDOW/DOOR TRIM (openings read as openings, controllably): wall openings now carry architectural trim, placed via one shared face-span helper (`wall-geometry.ts` `faceSpanBox`/`FaceSpan`, flat faces only — round bodies keep the bare recess). WINDOWS gain a projecting stone SILL + head LINTEL (square heads; arched/lancet keep their carved curve) and a timber MULLION GRID — `lightsWide`×`lightsHigh` panes (glazing-bar count = lights−1), a controllable param that DEFAULTS through the connectome/descriptor fold: `descriptorPatch` maps wealth→grid (poor a single crude light … opulent a fine leaded 3×3), so a window's pane count now varies by building type + prosperity instead of reading as a blank dark hole. DOORS render their already-MODELLED hardware — a stone THRESHOLD step always, plus a metal HANDLE (latch side, from the `handle` param) and optional LOCK/KNOCKER/BELL prims when those params are set. Every preset with openings recomposes; the golden cottage (has windows + a door) moves on all channels (pins updated); the stone-box golden (no openings) holds. (v26 — DORMER GEOMETRY FIX: front-gabled ("doghouse") dormers now poke PROUD of the roof slope instead of reading as an L-shaped pit. The old `dormerSolids` was a fixed-z horizontal slab spanning ridge→eave — on a steep roof (the tavern's pitch-1.5 slope) it buried at the ridge and floated a void over the eave, punching a concave notch into the roof. The new model is a compact body whose footprint DEPTH scales with pitch (so the slope climbs ~faceH across it: back edge buries flush, front pokes proud) and whose base sinks 0.8 below the slope so it always fuses into the roof solid — no floating overhang. Only the tavern carries dormers, so its composed sprite changes; the golden fixtures (plaster cottage, stone box) carry no dormer so their G-buffer hashes hold. (v25 — WALL PLANK ORIENTATION + REALISM: timber board texturing is now direction-aware — palisade staves paint the new `stave` work (upright round logs with per-log tone + barrel rounding + vertical grain, no more horizontal banding), gate leaves + hoarding breastworks paint the new `plank_v` work (upright boards), and the `plank`/`plank_v`/`board_batten` family gained per-board hashed tone + warm/cool tint, staggered butt joints and sparse knots (`material-surface.ts` `boardField`). Texture-only (no geometry change) — palisade/gate/hoarded-wall SPRITES change; the golden fixtures (plaster cottage, stone box) don't exercise timber plank so their G-buffer hashes hold. WP-W2 (piece cutter, same v25): the barrier render cutter cuts canonical wall rings into a FINITE piece vocabulary — √2 diagonal pieces (one (±1,±1) step) + 2-tile cardinal pieces, orientation-normalized to 4 bearings; self-tiling symmetric merlons (whole periods per piece — the global merlonPhase is retired); and tower orientation quantized to 8 octants — so a barrier sprite's geometry (merlon layout, diagonal/reversed cuts, tower octant) shifts vs the pre-W2 chunker. Curtain/tower composed sprites change (the golden fixtures carry no timber/masonry-curtain coverage, so their pinned G-buffers hold). (v24 — ROOF VOCABULARY + ROUND TESSELLATION: gambrel/mansard/saltbox/cross_gable are REAL geometry in `solids.ts` (no longer collapsed to gable/hip — the barn is now gambrel), tympana recess under the slope boards (kills the raking-edge z-fight stipple), and round solids (cylinder/cone/ellipsoid) tessellate by radius (`roundSegments`, chord ≈ 0.12 tiles) instead of the flat 32 — towers/domes/wells stop reading polygonal. Plus ARCHITECTURAL TRIM (`blueprint/parts/trim.ts`): two-stage stepped BUTTRESSES between the windows + braced corners on worship bodies (connectome-derived), and crenellated PARAPETS (breast + merlons, reusing the defensive-wall battlement builders) on flat-roofed towers/keeps. Barn + round buildings + church/tower/keep massing changed ⇒ invalidate cached sprites. (v23 — CHURCH: grounded WEST TOWER + broach spire over the entrance gable, and tall pointed LANCET windows on worship buildings.)))))))))

/**
 * Bump when WORLDGEN / preset output changes (footprints, placement, heights).
 * An autosave stamped with a different value is discarded on load → a fresh
 * world is generated. Distinct from SAVE_VERSION (which guards the save *schema*).
 */
export const WORLD_CONTENT_VERSION = 95;  // FLORA DENSITY DIAL + GROUND-COVER BASELINE — vegetation read sparse. (1) The dead style knob `floraDensity` (world-style.ts, declared since S0 with NO consumer) is WIRED: `World.applyBrush` resolves `worldStyleOf(tiles.worldSeed)` into a new optional `BrushContext.style`, and `placeVegetation` multiplies its authored base `density` AND `openUndergrowth` (capped <=1) by it — pure threshold change, hash rolls untouched, so per-(x,y,seed) determinism holds and a missing style = x1 = old behaviour. (2) Ground-cover baseline raised: grassland brush density 0.11->0.18 with the grassland canopy pool rebalanced toward wildflowers (tussock 0.66->0.61, oxeye-daisy 0.14->0.17, common-poppy 0.08->0.10 — ~2x effective wildflowers/tile); forest openUndergrowth 0.3->0.35, pine 0.25->0.35 (dense_forest untouched). (3) UNDERGROWTH_CLEAR_RADIUS 1.2->0.9 (roadside grass/flowers are good; TREE_CLEAR_RADIUS 2.2, treeline, wear halos and killing fields untouched). Vegetation entity counts/positions change on every world => discard older autosaves.
//                                          (prev 94) RIVERS R5 GROUND-BLEND — big dry-land riparian boulders (granite-boulder, entity scale ≥ 0.75 ≈ 1.5 m) now SETTLE INTO GRADE: (1) a mini level pad per boulder (`buildBoulderPadDeformations`, boulder-deformation.ts — disc radius 0.5·scale tiles, feather 0.75, 0.08 m settle, priority 8 = below ALL engineered ground) composed into the world deformation store; pads are map-pure by RE-DERIVING the riparian scatter with the generator's exact inputs (`map.riparianSeed`, a new GameMap field the generator stamps — maps without it, e.g. test stubs/studio grounds, get NO pads by construction). In-water riffle boulders are deliberately excluded (river incision priority 40 rules the bed; the contact line sits under the drawn water plane). (2) The contact TILE under each such boulder swaps to `dirt` at gen (map-generator riparian loop, `isTrampleEligible` ground only — permanent tile, NOT trample wear, which decays and would revert an untrafficked ring). Heightfield + tiles change near bank boulders on any world with fresh water ⇒ discard older autosaves. (prev 93 — CONNECTION-SPLIT REPAIR + SMITHY RE-MASS —(1) `repairConnectionSplits` (road-graph.ts, runs after `repairRoadDiagonalGaps`): the end-to-end invariant the individual road passes each assume — every seed-declared road connection is ONE 4-connected component. The inter-POI walker can end up riding a settlement's interior street; a later layout change re-routing that street (here: the smithy's door face moving south→east re-routed its street connector) silently split A↔B into two islands even though every pass succeeded. The repair floods from the road cell nearest `from`, and if it never comes within 3 tiles of `to`, BFS-carves a minimal legal land connector (never water / caller-flagged obstacles) between the closest cells of the two components, stamping `dirt_road` + WARNING (`connection repair FIRED`). (2) Smithy re-massed to its TTI reference: deep stone range entered through the EAST gable (cart door + flanking lights), forge rebuilt as an open-mouth chimney breast (new furnace `mouth: n|s|e|w` param) on the long south wall toward the rear, gableted ridge louver; tavern ground-floor taproom lights enlarged (1.2×1.3 m). Smithy door/collision cells + repair connectors shift roads on affected seeds ⇒ discard older autosaves. (prev 92 — BRIDGE ABUTMENTS + PROUD ARCH RING — a TTI reference run (pure text→image of each bridge type vs our grey massing, reference-library/tti/bridge-*) surfaced a convergent geometry gap: our composed spans ended flush at the footprint edge (a floating slab) where the model consistently grounds a bridge on bold battered end-blocks / wing-walls landing on the bank. New `abutment` part (`src/blueprint/parts/bridge.ts`, registered) = a stepped battered masonry end-block (wide foot → deck-width top, the deck-camber segmenting trick), and `arch_span` gained a `ringDepthM` param exposing the arch prim's ring depth. `buildBridgeObject` now stamps two abutments at the clear-span ends (in the +1-tile footprint margin, bed → deck underside, both stone & timber) and passes a proud `ringDepthM = ARCH_RING_M` (bumped 0.7→0.9 m, deck seating kept in sync via `riseM + ARCH_RING_M = clearZM`). World bridge geometry changes ⇒ discard older autosaves. (prev 91 — BRIDGES = ONE COHERENT PARAMETRIC OBJECT — a road×water crossing was scattered into a bank-lifted deck + independently-lifted pier & arch entities whose vertical scales never reconciled: supports sized in TRUE metric (clearance·reliefM) rendered ~1.6× too tall for the terrain's COMPRESSED vertical (terrainVerticalExaggeration 20 px/m vs sprites' PX_PER_METRE 32), so the deck floated at bank height while stub arches sat at the foot of towering piers — no coherent arcade. Now each crossing composes as ONE `bridge` blueprint entity (`buildBridgeObject`, crossing-structures.ts): a filled-spandrel stone arcade (or a timber trestle) with a parapeted, hump-backed deck RIDING the arch crowns, lifted ONCE to the bed elevation. Supports are sized in the terrain's compressed vertical (× zPxPerM/PX_PER_METRE) so they span the real bank→bed SCREEN gap. The `deck` part gained `baseZM` (vertical datum) + `camberM` (parabolic hump); `map-generator` threads `zPxPerM` (worldStyle.terrainVerticalExaggeration) into the crossing options. The legacy bridge_deck/bridge_pier/bridge_arch entity kinds retire → `bridge.tiles-vs-deck` diagnostic + settlement annex both query kind `'bridge'`. Crossing superstructure geometry + entity kinds change ⇒ discard older autosaves. (prev 90 — ROAD NETWORK 4-CONNECTIVITY REPAIR — independently-carved road sources (a settlement's own streets, the inter-POI approach graph, gate stitches/spurs) can meet DIAGONALLY: an approach road's endpoint anchors a tile off the street it joins, so the two touch only at a corner. A 4-neighbour flood (NPC walkability + the road-connectivity contract `carve-connections.test.ts`) then reads them as DISCONNECTED even though they visually touch (this was a deterministic red test since the #28 gate-stitch fix — the walker stops one diagonal step short). New `repairRoadDiagonalGaps` (road-graph.ts) runs after all road sources are carved: for each diagonally-adjacent road pair with neither shared orthogonal cell already road, it stamps ONE shared orthogonal filler as `dirt_road` — preferring walkable land, never over water/bridge/building/wall/green (the walker's own obstacle set). Extends the per-edge `orthogonalize` guarantee ACROSS sources. Road tiles gain filler cells at diagonal junctions on affected seeds ⇒ discard older autosaves. (prev 89 — BRIDGES & STAIRS SEAT ON THE VISIBLE WATER + STAIRS DE-PILE — river crossings sited/sized against the tile RASTER read as broken: roads carve 'bridge'/'dirt_road' over the channel (hiding it from a raster `isWater` read exactly at the crossing) and the widened/meandered ribbon spills past the walker's thin bridged run, so deck abutments sat in the visible water or beside it, and several roads climbing one riverbank each spawned a flight, jamming a knot of steps into a few tiles. FIX (mill-site WCV-87 pattern — consumers that must match the DRAWN water read the connectome, not the tile grid): `generateWithNoise` builds an authoritative `renderRiver` mask (the same W∝√Q disc swath the raster-widening + render-water-mask paint, captured BEFORE roads overwrite river tiles) and passes `renderWaterAt` (renderRiver ∪ ocean/lake) as the crossing/stoop/stair water signal. `detectCrossings` gains `bridgeAt`: each raster crossing run (seeded from the walker's `bridgeCells`, so tangential bankside contact invents NO spurious crossing) EXTENDS along the road over contiguous render-wet cells, so the deck covers the full ribbon and banks land render-dry by construction. `buildStairStructureEntities` enforces a 3-tile cross-edge min spacing between flight feet (stacked flights on ONE road exempt) — parallel roads' stairs no longer pile up. Verified via a synthetic span-scenario harness (`tests/helpers/span-scenario.ts` + `tests/unit/span-scenario.test.ts`) checking deck coverage/abutments/piers/stair spacing against render-water. Crossing + stair + stoop entity positions shift ⇒ discard older autosaves. (prev 88 — TRADE-BUILDING IDENTITIES — smithy/bakehouse/brewhouse/inn were all indistinguishable generic one-door rect bodies (they folded through `blueprintFromBuildingType`); they now have PINNED presets with bespoke craft massing. New shared `furnace` part (`parts/furnace.ts`, kind forge|oven|kiln) renders the heat-mass silhouette from existing prims (box/cylinder/cone) — smithy = stone forge bench across an open front + a tall brick flue; bakehouse = a domed masonry bread oven bulging from the gable + flue stub; brewhouse = a tall oast kiln (stone drum + conical tiled cap + timber cowl) that vents the mash steam. inn = a larger 2-storey jettied range over a stone base (a bigger tavern). Settlements rostering thes